## ⚡ Power Distribution

<div align="center">

| Voltage | Components |
|--------|------------|
| 🔹 **3.3V Rail** | AD8232, MAX30102, TFT Display, ADS1115, DHT11, Toggle Switch |
| 🔸 **5V Rail** | AD620, TL072, LM358 |

</div>

---

## 🎚️ Signal Conditioning (Gain Configuration)

- 🔹 **100kΩ Gain Resistors**
  - TL072 → Pin 1 ↔ Pin 2  
  - LM358 → Pin 1 ↔ Pin 2  

- 🔹 Additional Gain Path  
  - Pin 2 → GND  

> 📈 Used for **signal amplification & filtering of ECG signals**

---

## 🧩 Components Used

### 🔹 Core Controller
- ESP32 (30-pin)

### 🔹 Analog Front-End
- AD8232 (ECG Module)
- AD620 (Instrumentation Amplifier)
- TL072 (Op-Amp)
- LM358 (Op-Amp)

### 🔹 Data Acquisition
- ADS1115 (16-bit ADC)

### 🔹 Sensors
- MAX30102 (Heart Rate & SpO₂)
- DHT11 (Temperature & Humidity)

### 🔹 Output Modules
- TFT SPI Display
- RGB LED

### 🔹 Input Controls
- Rotary Encoder
- Toggle Switch

### 🔹 Passive Components
- 100kΩ Resistors (Gain)
- 10kΩ Pull-up Resistor
- 220Ω Resistors (LED Current Limiting)

---

## 🧪 Design Notes

- 🔁 I2C Bus is shared between **ADS1115 & MAX30102**
- ⚠️ Keep analog wiring **short & shielded** to reduce noise
- ⚡ Ensure proper **common grounding**
- 📊 Optimized for **low-noise ECG signal acquisition**

